<title>USA: Best Products secures interim financing.</title>
<headline>Best Products secures interim financing.</headline>
<dateline>RICHMOND, Va. 1996-10-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Best Products Co said Tuesday the U.S. Bankruptcy Court here approved $195 million in interim financing, allowing the company to resume normal operations.</p>
<p>The ruling allows Best Products to use $195 milion of a $250 million unsecured debtor-in-possession facility the company obtained from CIT Group/Business Credit Inc.</p>
<p>The facility includes a $100 million sublimit for letters of credit, the company said.</p>
<p>A hearing to allow Best Products to make full use of the facility is scheduled for October 10.</p>
